Add support for the pi coding agent

Integrate the pi coding agent (https://pi.dev) alongside claude and
codex.  Like `rumpel claude`, `rumpel pi` installs the host's pinned pi
version into the pod, copies the local pi auth/config in, and runs pi's
TUI in-pod over a `/pi` PTY WebSocket.

Because pi is an npm package (not a self-contained binary), the prepared
image provisions a Node.js runtime: it reuses an already-new-enough
node, else installs one via the base image's package manager (apt/apk),
falling back to a standalone Node v22.x download, then `npm install -g`s
the pinned package.

pi auth/config (~/.pi/agent/{auth,settings,models}.json) is copied into
the pod via a new `ensure_pi_config` daemon RPC, and the workspace is
pre-trusted so the TUI runs unattended.  Integration tests exercise the
in-pod pi against the Anthropic API through the existing LLM cache
proxy.
